 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S5-P02-T062 (version timeline / as-of / old-vs-new diff API; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Sixty-second task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S5-P02). Adds the user-facing read layer over the document version chain: a version timeline, a locatable old-vs-new diff, an as-of history query, and old-version replay -- so a user can SEE the real change, the historical state, and the source location. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a read-only API library, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/version_asof_api.py: version_timeline (folds renders into SUBSTANTIVE versions -- a noise-only re-render never becomes a version -- each carrying its noise-stripped body snapshot), diff_payload (a line-level LOCATABLE diff classifying every change add/delete/modify with its line number and exact text, computed over the noise-stripped body so TEMPLATE NOISE IS NEVER SHOWN), as_of (the version in force as of a date, by parsed date, NEVER a future version -- reuses T056), and replay_version / replay_is_idempotent (deterministic reconstruction of an OLD version, idempotent across replays). Reuses T026 version_engine (noise rules + version decision) and T056 coverage_asof (as-of resolver) rather than re-implementing them. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S5-P02-T062/: version_asof_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S5-P02-T062/test-results/version_asof_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): a substantive v2-vs-v1 diff is exactly {add:1, delete:1, modify:1} each located to its line with the correct old/new text; a noise-only re-render yields an EMPTY diff and adds no version, while a raw un-stripped diff of the SAME pair surfaces 6 noise lines (proving the stripping is load-bearing); real article text is never stripped; an old version replays byte-for-byte and is idempotent over 3 runs; and as_of never returns a future version -- 0 future-leakage and 0 oracle-disagreements over a 288-sample battery, while a deliberately-future resolver is caught on 70 samples. Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S5-P02-T061 (full-text + semantic rerank benchmark and ADR; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Sixty-first task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S5-P02). Benchmarks full-text search and a semantic rerank, and adopts a semantic layer only when it earns its cost -- never prematurely. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a benchmark and decision record, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/fts_benchmark.py provides a deterministic full-text ranker (IDF-weighted overlap), MRR and recall@k metrics over a fixed query set, and decide_adopt -- the ADR rule that adopts a semantic layer only if it both IMPROVES the fixed query set AND does not bypass structured filters. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S5-P02-T061/: benchmark_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S5-P02-T061/test-results/benchmark_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): on a 24-document corpus with a 6-query fixed set, the FTS baseline scores recall@5 0.875 (a genuine miss -- the 低温雨雪 query misses a doc that uses the synonym 冰冻灾害); a synonym-aware semantic reranker raises recall@5 to 0.917 and respects structured filters, so it is ADOPTED; a non-improving reranker and a filter-bypassing reranker are both REJECTED; and the rule is a true AND, since an improving-but-filter-bypassing reranker and a non-improving filter-respecting reranker are both rejected. Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
